m.t: Discord always seems like the place for *those* communities and *those* people.
People are still themselves, but the whole context of the site just puts them all into a sort of clique.
They reveal themselves much more there than on other social media, and who can blame them?

Sigh... Discord just... makes everything seem like an in-group and an out-group. The entire contents of it are inaccessible to everyone who isn't a member of it. Even the community servers aren't some forums you can just go and read. They're chat rooms for specific communities.

It should feel more open. Discord is the heart of every stale website and community ever. Trust me, I've seen, like, what? Two or three examples? If you come across a dead-looking website with a Discord link, you could easily bet your life it's active and live to see another day.
Yes, it feels very overwhelming
